 <p><img src=http://www.planettom.com/eq/dest.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D7CFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uaislinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aislinn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.winterblood.com/portraits/cimmarose_icon.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guilds/HTML Editor<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/staff.gif></span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#E09C5F>(6/29/01 11:06:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New PVP server</span><hr size=1> The problem with any &quot;pvp server&quot; is that the only people willing to play in a world where there are no penalties for grief-playing, are grief-players themselves. By definition, &quot;pvp servers&quot; mean pairings with &quot;candyland&quot; servers, where griefers still exist and get away with slightly less blatant anti-social behaviour, only non-griefers are virtually powerless to stop them.<br>
<br>
Dichotomous pvp/blue server/mirror systems don't work (ask anyone who currently plays UO on an American server). This is precisely why so many of the next-gen games are coming up with inventive ways of mixing pvp and non-pvp on the same server, allowing for a player-enforced societal system in addition to a game-enforced rep system AND a GM-enforced ruleset. <p><p><font size="1" face="Verdana">Cimmarose's player<br>
</font><a href="http://www.winterblood.com"><font size="1" face="Verdana">www.winterblood.com</font></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E1DF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uaislinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aislinn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.winterblood.com/portraits/cimmarose_icon.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guilds/HTML Editor<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/staff.gif></span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#E09C5F>(6/29/01 1:02:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New PVP server</span><hr size=1> Elaborating on that, as I think more on this... when UO was flagging, OSI would often open up an extra server around holidays and as special promotions that seem similar to this pvp server, they would be anything-goes type arenas. Griefers loved those sort of servers, but they tend to get bored. After awhile, it's not that much fun preying on people that will not only fight back, but have a good chance of winning. (That's the big difference between griefers and pvpers... anyway I digress :) I just wondered if anyone else remembered those gankfest promotional servers in UO...<br>
<br>
