</font><a href="http://www.winterblood.com"><font size="1" face="Verdana">www.winterblood.com</font></a></p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uaislinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aislinn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.winterblood.com/portraits/cimmarose_icon.gif BORDER=0> at: 6/29/01 1:09:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D7CFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/umemak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>memak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Defender<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif></span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#E09C5F>(6/29/01 2:29:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: New PVP server</span><hr size=1> <i>"The problem with any "pvp server" is that the only people willing to play in a world where there are no penalties for grief-playing, are grief-players themselves. "</i><br>
<br>
This is simply not ture.  By far the majority of players on PvP servers are very courtious, and the communities are much tighter and help each other considerably more -- this is the nature of conflict; it binds us toward a mutual goal.  Further, PvP can be a very nice diversion from the monotony of the day to day PvE grind on blue server.  Finally, the PvP servers have far more actual role players, perhaps because the environment makes more sense.<br>
<br>
That said, PvP in EQ has issues.  Aside from class balance issues which are very evident in the post 45 levels, cross-teaming was a huge problem on Vallon Zek -- Probably the biggest reason I chose to return to Mith Marr.  SZ seems to have addressed that problem very nicely.  <br>
<br>
Ganking, especially at lower levels, was also a problem.  Unfortunately, Verant's solution of no pvp pre level 6 and then open war with no holds barred is, IMHO, doomed to catastrophic failure.  While this would work wonderfully for the vast majority, a few people will badly abuse the system and the end result will be many upset people.  Verant thinks the server populace can solve their own problems with gankers, but some people simply get off on ruining the game for others and will do it habitually.  Corpse camping, training, causing exp deaths, exploiting weak rules and game mechanics -- I saw it all on VZ way too much, and there were actually GMs trying to help there...<br>
<br>
The bottom line is that PvP certainly isn't for everyone (look at server populations), but you have to try it -- for a while -- to really get a feel.  Going today and starting a new character on SZ and playing to level 20 isn't going to give you a good feel.  SZ is a chaotic mess with all the people experimenting and the new PvP rule set.  Sounds fun to alot of people and completely "unfun" to many others.<br>
<br>
Too bad Verant still won't let us move our chars -- I have a feeling I'd enjoy SZ alot more than VZ with the new rule set, but starting over AGAIN?!  Nope.  Not in EQ.<br>
